  "prompt": "I scored 570 in neet 2 . What would be my expected rank, in total from neet 1 & 2?",
  "response": "Predicting an exact rank based on your NEET score can be challenging, as it depends on various factors, including the overall performance of other candidates, the difficulty of the exam, and the number of students appearing for NEET. \n\nHowever, based on previous years' trends, a score of 570 typically falls within a range that could correspond to a rank anywhere from around 8,000 to 25,000, depending on the specific exam year and the overall performance of the candidates. \n\nFor a more accurate estimate, you may refer to the official NEET result statistics released by the National Testing Agency (NTA) or consult rank estimation tools or resources available from educational websites or coaching institutes that analyze past NEET results. \n\nKeep in mind that cutoff marks and ranks can vary from year to year, so it's best to check the latest information once the results are officially released.",
